30/05/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- In response to concerns over its religious roots, the ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP) tapped two prominent Social Democrats to run for the July 22nd parliamentary elections. Ertugrul Gunay, former general secretary of the main opposition Republican People's Party (CHP), and Haluk Ozdalga, former general secretary of the Democratic Left Party, addressed AKP lawmakers Tuesday (May 29th) after being introduced by Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan. Gunay, a key figure on the left, has been a vocal opponent of the CHP leadership. (Radikal, Aksam, Vatan, Hurriyet, Turkishpress.com, Zaman - 30/05/07; Reuters - 29/05/07)
